      "text": "Recorded by Beth Dudek.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-003",
      "start": 18.5,
      "end": 21.88,
      "text": "ESAP's Fables. The Peacock and the Crane.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-004",
      "start": 23.38,
      "end": 27.3,
      "text": "A Peacock taunted a crane with the dullness of her plumage.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-005",
      "start": 28.08,
      "end": 35.88,
      "text": "Look at my brilliant colors, said she, and see how much finer they are than your poor feathers.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-006",
      "start": 37.16,
      "end": 48.22,
      "text": "I am not denying, replied the Crane, that yours are far gayer than mine, but when it comes to flying, I can soar into the clouds.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-007",
      "start": 48.98,
      "end": 53.66,
      "text": "Whereas you are confined to the earth like any dung hill cack.",
      "note": ""
    },
    {
      "id": "line-008",
      "start": 54.9,
      "end": 57.0,
      "text": "End of the Peacock and the Crane.",
      "note": ""
    }
  ],
